# Rent-a-Nerd

> A quirky services company offering premium golf experiences and family tech support - because sometimes you just need a nerd.

---

## Overview

Rent-a-Nerd is a service-based business concept under [[Kikman Enterprises]] that leverages technical and golf expertise in unconventional ways. The brand embraces the "nerd" identity while providing genuinely useful (and sometimes absurd) services.

**Tagline Ideas:**
- "Your nerd, on demand"
- "Nerds you can trust"
- "Technical support for life"

---

## Service Lines

### 1. Golf Caddy Services

**Concept:** Professional-ish caddy services for casual golfers who want the country club experience without the country club membership.

#### Service Tiers

| Tier | Price | Includes |
|------|-------|----------|
| **Basic Caddy** | $50/round | Bag carrying, club selection advice, moral support |
| **Pro Caddy** | $100/round | Above + yardage book, read greens, strategy coaching |
| **VIP Experience** | $200/round | Above + snacks, beverages, photos, post-round summary |

#### Target Market
- Corporate golf outings wanting to impress
- Birthday/bachelor party golf experiences
- Casual golfers wanting to feel fancy
- People learning the game who want guidance

#### Operations
- [ ] Recruit golf-knowledgeable contractors
- [ ] Create training materials
- [ ] Develop booking system
- [ ] Set service areas (local courses first)

---

### 2. Fake Golf Partner / Witness Services

**Concept:** The most absurd service offering - we'll lie about your golf performance and back it up.

#### Service Options

| Service | Price | What You Get |
|---------|-------|--------------|
| **Witness Package** | $25 | We'll confirm you hit that shot |
| **Scorecard Validation** | $50 | Official-looking attestation of your score |
| **Full Partner** | $150/round | Play with you, witness everything, vouch for any claims |
| **Highlight Reel** | $100 | Video "evidence" of your best shots (may include creative editing) |

#### Legal Disclaimer
*"For entertainment purposes only. Rent-a-Nerd makes no claims about the accuracy of witnessed events. Use of our witness services for gambling purposes is prohibited and also hilarious."*

#### Marketing Angle
- Lean into the absurdity
- Target as gag gifts
- Social media viral potential
- Golf buddy pranks

#### Honest Use Cases
- Friends who exaggerate - now you have "proof"
- Hole-in-one witnesses (legitimate)
- Content creation assistance
- Corporate team building humor

---

### 3. Family Tech Support

**Concept:** On-demand tech support for families, particularly helping parents and grandparents with technology.

**Tagline:** "Bring your family's tech problems to us!"

#### Service Offerings

| Service | Price | Description |
|---------|-------|-------------|
| **Phone Support** | $25/30min | Remote troubleshooting via phone/video |
| **Remote Session** | $50/hr | Screen share problem solving |
| **Home Visit** | $100/hr | In-person tech support (local) |
| **Tech Tutoring** | $75/hr | Teach skills (not just fix problems) |
| **Device Setup** | $75 flat | New phone/tablet/computer setup |
| **Monthly Plan** | $50/mo | Unlimited phone support, 1 remote session |

#### Common Requests
- "My email isn't working"
- "How do I use this new phone?"
- "The printer won't print"
- "I think I have a virus"
- "Can you set up my new TV?"
- "Help me video call my grandkids"

#### Target Market
- Adults with elderly parents
- Parents themselves who are tech-challenged
- Small families wanting on-call support
- Gift purchasers (gift cards for parents)

#### Differentiators vs Geek Squad etc.
| Factor | Big Box | Rent-a-Nerd |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| Price | $$$$ | $$ |
| Wait time | Days | Hours |
| Personal touch | Corporate | Your nerd |
| Patience level | Rushed | Unlimited |
| Follow-up | Rare | Standard |

#### Operations
- [ ] Develop service menu
- [ ] Create troubleshooting guides for common issues
- [ ] Set up scheduling system
- [ ] Define service areas for home visits
- [ ] Insurance/liability considerations

